  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Meyer's NT Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 13:12",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "Ἐπὶ τῇ διδαχῇ τ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "Κυρίου",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] For he rightly saw, both in that announcement of punishment by Paul, and in the fate of his sorcerer, something which had a connection with the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "doctrine of the Lord",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (that is, with the doctrine which Christ caused to be proclaimed by His ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "apostles;",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " see on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 8:25",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). Its announcer had shown such a marvellous familiarity with the counsel of God, and its opponent had suddenly experienced such a severe punishment, that he was ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "astonished at the doctrine",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", with which so evident a divine judgment was connected. Comp. on the connection of the judgment concerning the doctrine with the miracle beheld, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Mark 1:27",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἐπίστευσεν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " obviously supposes the reception of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "baptism;",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " comp. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 4:4",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 11:21",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 19:18",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Whether the sorcerer afterwards became a believer",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " the text does not, indeed, inform us; but the presumption of a future conversion is contained in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἄχρι καιροῦ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 13:11",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and therefore the question is to be answered in the affirmative; for Paul spoke that ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἄχρι καιροῦ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ": ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ὅριον τῇ γνώμῃ διδούς",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", Oecumenius. The Tübingen criticism has indeed condemned the miraculous element in this story, and the story itself as an invented and exaggerated counterpart of the encounter of Peter with Simon Magus, chap. 8—a judgment in which the denial of miracles in general, and the assumption of dogmatic motives on the part of the author, are the controlling presuppositions (see Baur and Zeller; comp. also Schneckenburger, p. 53).",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  {
