        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). Farrar thinks that if so marked a person had become a lifelong convert, we should have heard of him as such in other writings, Renan says, \"La conversion d'un Romain de cet ordre, a cette epoque est chose absolument inadmissible.\" Alford and Olshausen speak doubtfully. Lange and Howson and Meyer look upon him as a genuine convert. The 'Speaker's Commentary' speaks of him as \"the first fruits of heathenism.\" ",
        "children": []
